cs.BIO, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CE, cs.NE 

This paper involves the use of DNA for data storage and processing, which falls under the category of computational biology (cs.BIO). The use of addressing oligonucleotides and downstream enzymatic and biological processing suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The proposal of more advanced methods involving protein/DNA complexes and atomic force microscopy/nano-pore schemes suggests a focus on computer engineering (cs.CE) and neural networks (cs.NE) for data readout.
